Dom här vågar jag inte tanka , jag får skumma attacker hela tiden, brandväggen varnar.
Och jag vet inte vad ....... Kotor är, jämfört med den andra.

Så här ser infon om attacken ut;
Event description 

Multiple FTP servers employ a glob(3) function, which is used to expand shorthand notation into complete file names. Implementations of the c-shell globbing code are vulnerable to a buffer overflow. By supplying to the FTP server a pattern string containing a set of braces {} followed by an overly long string, a remote attacker can overflow a buffer in the execbrc function and execute arbitrary code on the FTP server. In order to exploit this vulnerability, the attacker must be able to create directories on the FTP server.
